      "stepsHeading": "How to plan a lesson using our resources and adapt them for your classroom.",
      "steps": {
        "step1": {
          "title": "Find the right lesson",
          "image": {
            "asset": {
              "_id": "image-0b79b8db82cc4371d94b94a4ce58513ba7d67bfd-4867x2946-jpg",
              "url": "https://cdn.sanity.io/images/cuvjke51/production/0b79b8db82cc4371d94b94a4ce58513ba7d67bfd-4867x2946.jpg"
            }
          },
          "bodyPortableText": [
            {
              "_key": "c5fd219ba3cb",
              "_type": "block",
              "children": [
                {
                  "_key": "69bfb50b933f0",
                  "_type": "span",
                  "marks": [],
                  "text": "Mitch your intended learning outcomes to the core content summary at the top of each Oak lesson overview page. Familiarise yourself with the resources by clicking through the slides, scanning the transcript and reviewing the quiz questions."
                }
              ],
              "markDefs": [],
              "style": "normal"
            }
          ],
          "cta": null
        },
        "step2": {
          "title": "Tailor your explanation",
          "image": null,
          "bodyPortableText": [
            {
              "_key": "43a12519987c",
              "_type": "block",
              "children": [
                {
                  "_key": "d13f3d5c4f7d0",
                  "_type": "span",
                  "marks": [],
                  "text": "Watch the video to inspire and refine how you will explain new content. Consider your pupils’ current levels of understanding, gaps in their knowledge, what they have learnt recently and what they will learn next when personalising your explanation."
                }
              ],
              "markDefs": [],
              "style": "normal"
            }
          ],
          "cta": null
        },
        "step3": {
          "title": "Adapt the tasks for your class",
          "image": null,
          "bodyPortableText": [
            {
              "_key": "0f3d6c013b26",
              "_type": "block",
              "children": [
                {
                  "_key": "48afeb29a02e0",
                  "_type": "span",
                  "marks": [],
                  "text": "Build in or remove additional scaffolding and support to suit the learning needs of your pupils. Decide how your class will complete each task and consider how you’ll divide your available time between tasks, explanations and quizzes."
                }
              ],
              "markDefs": [],
              "style": "normal"
            }
          ],
          "cta": null
        },
        "step4": {
          "title": "Teach the lesson",
          "image": {
            "asset": {
              "_id": "image-0b79b8db82cc4371d94b94a4ce58513ba7d67bfd-4867x2946-jpg",
              "url": "https://cdn.sanity.io/images/cuvjke51/production/0b79b8db82cc4371d94b94a4ce58513ba7d67bfd-4867x2946.jpg"
            }
          },
          "bodyPortableText": [
            {
              "_key": "4af9862cbb4b",
              "_type": "block",
              "children": [
                {
                  "_key": "3c2f4ab44df20",
                  "_type": "span",
                  "marks": [],
                  "text": "Now you have reviewed, adapted and prepared the resources, it’s time to teach the lesson! While you’re teaching, try to tweak task formats, explanation wordings and check for understanding questions to ensure you are responding to the needs of your pupils."
                }
              ],
              "markDefs": [],
              "style": "normal"
            }
          ],
          "cta": null
        }
      },
